label.value: Pancreatic Neuroendocrine Tumor Pathologic Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v8

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of a pancreatic neuroendocrine tumor, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.

label.value: Pancreatic Neuroendocrine Tumor pM1 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Pancreatic neuroendocrine tumor with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Pancreatic Neuroendocrine Tumor pM1a TNM Finding v8

value.value: Pancreatic neuroendocrine tumor with metastasis confined to liver. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Pancreatic Neuroendocrine Tumor pM1b TNM Finding v8

value.value: Pancreatic neuroendocrine tumor with metastasis in at least one extrahepatic site (e.g., lung, ovary, nonregional lymph node, peritoneum, bone). (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Pancreatic Neuroendocrine Tumor pM1c TNM Finding v8

value.value: Pancreatic neuroendocrine tumor with both hepatic and extrahepatic metastases. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: 3q

value.value: Distal (long) arm of chromosome 3

label.value: Pancreatic Neuroendocrine Tumor Pathologic Primary Tumor TNM Finding v8

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of a pancreatic neuroendocrine tumor, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor.

label.value: Pancreatic Neuroendocrine Tumor pTX TNM Finding v8

value.value: Pancreatic neuroendocrine tumor in which the primary tumor cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Pancreatic Neuroendocrine Tumor pT1 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Pancreatic neuroendocrine tumor limited to the pancreas and measuring less than 2 cm. Limited to the pancreas means there is no invasion of adjacent organs (stomach, spleen, colon, adrenal gland) or the wall of large vessels (celiac axis or the superior mesenteric artery). Extension of tumor into peripancreatic adipose tissue is not a basis for staging. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Pancreatic Neuroendocrine Tumor pT2 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Pancreatic neuroendocrine tumor limited to the pancreas and measuring 2-4 cm. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Pancreatic Neuroendocrine Tumor pT3 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Pancreatic neuroendocrine tumor limited to the pancreas and measuring more than 4 cm; or tumor invading the duodenum or bile duct. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Pancreatic Neuroendocrine Tumor pT4 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Pancreatic neuroendocrine tumor invading adjacent organs (stomach, spleen, colon, adrenal gland) or the wall of large vessels (celiac axis or the superior mesenteric artery). (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Pancreatic Neuroendocrine Tumor Pathologic Regional Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v8

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of a pancreatic neuroendocrine tumor, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

label.value: Pancreatic Neuroendocrine Tumor pNX TNM Finding v8

value.value: Pancreatic neuroendocrine tumor in which the regional lymph nodes cannot be assessed.  (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Pancreatic Neuroendocrine Tumor pN0 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Pancreatic neuroendocrine tumor without regional lymph node involvement. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Pancreatic Neuroendocrine Tumor pN1 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Pancreatic neuroendocrine tumor with regional lymph node involvement. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: 4q

value.value: Distal (long) arm of chromosome 4

label.value: Pancreatic Neuroendocrine Tumor by AJCC v8 Stage

value.value: A term that refers to the staging of a pancreatic neuroendocrine tumor, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system. This staging system applies to well-differentiated neuroendocrine tumors arising in the pancreas. Carcinomas of the pancreas, including high-grade (grade 3), poorly differentiated neuroendocrine carcinomas are not staged using this staging system. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Stage I Pancreatic Neuroendocrine Tumor AJCC v8

value.value: Stage I includes: T1, N0, M0. T1: Tumor limited to the pancreas and measuring less than 2 cm. N0: No regional lymph node involvement. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Stage II Pancreatic Neuroendocrine Tumor AJCC v8

value.value: Stage II includes: (T2, N0, M0); (T3, N0, M0). T2: Tumor limited to the pancreas and measuring 2-4 cm. T3: Tumor limited to the pancreas and measuring more than 4 cm; or tumor invading the duodenum or bile duct. N0: No regional lymph node involvement. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Stage III Pancreatic Neuroendocrine Tumor AJCC v8

value.value: Stage III includes: (T4, N0, M0); (Any T, N1, M0). T4: Tumor invading adjacent organs (stomach, spleen, colon, adrenal gland) or the wall of large vessels (celiac axis or the superior mesenteric artery). N0: No regional lymph node involvement. N1: Regional lymph node involvement. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Stage IV Pancreatic Neuroendocrine Tumor AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IV includes: Any T, Any N, M1. M1: Distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Brunner's Gland Hyperplasia

value.value: A rare hyperplastic lesion of Brunner's gland in the duodenum. Although it is usually asymptomatic and discovered incidentally during upper gastrointestinal endoscopy, it may cause hemorrhage.

label.value: Urine Protein Electrophoresis

label.value: Urine Immunofixation Electrophoresis
